Numerical quantity perceived from the data graphics

Mahbubul Majumder, PhD
Feb 27, 2019

Numerical summary of data

  • Measures of center

    • mean
    • median
    • mode
    • quartiles/percentiles

  • Measures of dispersion

    • Range
    • Variance and standard deviation
    • IQR

  • Other measures

    • skewness
    • kurtosis
    • correlation/ linearity
    • trend/ slope

  • Comparisons

    • differences in all the measures
    • proportions and ratios
    • spatial relations
    • grouping/ classification

Mosaic plot

  • what do we get from this plot?
  • we perceive
    • correlation between two categorical variables
    • proportion within class
    • odds ratio

Mosaic plot and odds ratio

  • titanic survival data

           0   1
  female 127 339
  male   682 161

  • survival ratio

    • RF = 339/127 = 2.67
    • RM = 161/682 = 0.24

  • odds ratio

    • OR = RF/RM
      = (339*682)/(161*127)
      = 11.31
